      "span_text": "It is also possible, considering the proximity of this structure to the site of proteolytic cleavage, that the membranous whorls mediate the process of enzymatic cleavage either because they contain proteolytic enzymes that are released during the processes of fertilization or because they regulate the penetration of exogenous proteolytic enzyme through the pores present in these membranes  ."
